cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with face recognition using deep neural networks and proposes a method for learning a feature representation that is invariant to pose. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a multi-source multi-task DNN, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a synthesis network for generating non-frontal views is related to image synthesis, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with disentangling identity and pose, which is related to multimedia analysis and processing, falling under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of a Siamese network for feature alignment is related to neural networks, falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
